                    <h2 id="mal-checklist">Quick Checklist</h2>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Encrypt or encode all shellcode and strings</li>
                        <li>Use dynamic API resolution (hashing) to hide imports</li>
                        <li>Avoid RWX memory — use RW then RX, or heap allocation</li>
                        <li>Implement sleep/delay to bypass sandbox analysis</li>
                        <li>Use legitimate-looking C2 domains with valid SSL</li>
                        <li>Implement jitter in beacon intervals</li>
                        <li>Test against multiple AV engines before deployment</li>
                        <li>Use process injection to hide in trusted processes</li>
                        <li>Implement multiple persistence mechanisms</li>
                        <li>Clean up logs and artifacts after execution</li>
                        <li>Use domain fronting or CDN for C2 if possible</li>
                        <li>Consider LOLBAS (Living Off The Land Binaries) instead of custom payloads</li>
                        <li>Document IOCs for your own payloads (for cleanup and reporting)</li>
                    </ul>

                    <blockquote>
                        "EDR is just a fancy syslog collector if you know which APIs to unhook. The best malware isn't sophisticated — it's just patient, quiet, and boring enough that nobody looks at it twice."
                    </blockquote>
